      <exercise permid="kIz">
        <statement>
          <p permid="fRC">
            Just like we did for groups, we can take the direct product of rings.  For example, the ring <m>\Z_2 \times \Z_3</m> contains 6 elements.  We add and multiply elements wise.
          </p>

          <p permid="LYL">
            For which <m>m</m> and <m>n</m> is the ring <m>\Z_m \times \Z_n</m> an integral domain?
          </p>
