          Show that their Cartesian product is a ring if we define addition and multiplication in <m>R \times S</m> by

          <ol permid="Ccm">
            <li permid="ixQ">
              <p permid="hGS">
                <m>(r, s) + (r', s') = ( r + r', s + s')</m>
              </p>
            </li>

            <li permid="OEZ">
              <p permid="NOb">
                <m>(r, s)(r', s') = ( rr', ss')</m>
              </p>
